	<text>
		<body>
			<div type="entry">
				<pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary01_0.jpg"/>
				<dateline><date>&amp;gt;Sunday 24</date>.</dateline>
				<p xml:id="a1">The <name type="weather">day was gloomy</name> - sadly overcast -
						<name type="weather">air windy &amp; this evening it commenced
						snowing.</name> We had a preaching by our Chaplain. "Rebellion is as the sin
					of witchcraft," the text. This afternoon, <persName key="George Shorkley"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper002"
						>Shorkleley</persName>, <persName key="Jacob G. Beaver"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper003"
						>Beaver</persName> &amp; I took a stroll through the <placeName
						key="Navy Yard"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnpl057"
						>navy yard</placeName>, <placeName>town &amp; </placeName>
					<placeName>cemetery</placeName>. Everything has an air of decay. </p>
				<p xml:id="a2">The <placeName key="Navy Yard"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnpl057"
						>navy yard </placeName>does not look like it did when I first saw it last
					spring. The old Battery looks natural enough. So the
						<placeName>Cemetery</placeName>. There are the graves of the
						<persName>Randalls</persName>, [?] &amp; many old familiar names. As we came
					out of the <placeName>cemetery</placeName>, we met an
						<placeName>officer</placeName> with a [squad?] of men from the cavalry
					Regiment going to dig a grave. </p>
				<pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary02.jpg"/>
				<fw><placeName>Anapolis Md. Camp Burnside</placeName><lb/>
					<date> November Sunday 24 1861.</date></fw>
				<p xml:id="a3">This evening,<persName key="Thomas Grier"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper076"
						> Tom Grier </persName>and I went to the <placeName>Presbyterian
						Church</placeName> &amp; came home through<name type="weather"> rain and
						snow</name>. We saw several handsome ladies, one in particular. I got
					vaccinated yesterday, &amp; this evening it itches considerable I have two
					slight scars on my arm, but they are very slight.</p>
			</div>
